<div id="sub-main" >
	<div id="wiki-content-block">

	
		


<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;"> <h3>Calamity Ring</h3> </td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/file/Dark-Souls-3/calamity_ring.png" alt="calamity ring" width="100"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td> <p>&nbsp;</p> 
      <blockquote> 
       <p>A ring made from the orange eye of a calamitous dragon. Receive double damage.</p> 
       <p>This ring has no useful powers, and is merely a symbol of dragon worship, a thing quietly passed down amongst its most fervent adherents, some of whom become convinced the task has been bestowed upon them as a sacred duty.</p> 
      </blockquote> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;<strong>Calamity Ring</strong> is a <a class="wiki_link" href="/Rings" title="Dark Souls 3 Rings">Ring</a> in Dark Souls 3. This is a returning item in the Dark Souls series, originally obtained from killing <a class="wiki_link wiki_tooltip" title="Dark Souls 3 Black Dragon Kalameet" href="https://darksouls.wiki.fextralife.com/Black+Dragon+Kalameet" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Black Dragon Kalameet</a>&nbsp;in the first game, <a class="wiki_link wiki_tooltip" title="Dark Souls" href="https://darksouls.wiki.fextralife.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dark Souls</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc0" class="bonfire"><a name="x--item Usage"></a>Calamity Ring Effect</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Reduces Absorptions by 100%</li> 
 <li>Weight: 0.8</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc1" class="bonfire"><a name="x--item Locations"></a>Where to Find Calamity Ring</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Use the Path of the Dragon <a class="wiki_link" href="/Gestures" title="Dark Souls 3 Gestures">Gesture</a>&nbsp;in front of the dragon statue after the&nbsp;Dragon-Kin Mausoleum bonfire in <a class="wiki_link" href="/Archdragon+Peak" title="Dark Souls 3 Archdragon Peak">Archdragon Peak</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc2" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Notes"></a>Notes</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Similar to the ring of the same name in the original Dark Souls, dropped by the black dragon Kalameet.</li> 
 <li>Does not affect fall damage</li> 
 <li>The ring has no real purpose, and is simply used to make the game harder.</li> 
 <li>Item could be used to troll new players if dropped, making their experience more difficult by taking in more damage.</li> 
 <li>Affects other absorption-reducing rings, i.e. any of the Clutch Rings, and makes them reduce absorption twice as much as they would normally, from 15% less to 30% less, and so on and so forth. This can be used to stack up damage taken until you effectively get one-shot by most things.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc3" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Trivia"></a>Trivia</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Trivia goes here</li> 
</ul> 
